def is_valid_triangle(a, b, c):
    if a + b > c and a + c > b and b + c > a:
        return True
    return False

Create a Python boolean function named is_valid_triangle that takes the length of three sides segments (a, b, c) and checks if they can form a valid triangle.  For this to be true the sides must satify the triangle inequality theorem.

The function should return True if the sides can form a valid triangle,  and False otherwise.

Triangle Inequality Theorem.

Three sides a, b and c form a valid triangle if and only if all of the following conditions are true:

a + b > c
a + c > b
b + c > a
